<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>GCS vs PCS</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display&family=DM+Sans:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <style>
    :root {
      --red:       #D7282F;
      --navy:      #1F1F55;
      --grey:      #86828B;
      --silver:    #C9C4C4;
      --purple:    #6D3A85;
      --slate:     #B8CED9;
      --navy-dark: #141430;
    }

    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    body {
      background: var(--navy-dark);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
      font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    }

    .card {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 880px;
      background: var(--navy);
      border-radius: 16px;
      overflow: hidden;
      box-shadow: 0 32px 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.55), 0 0 0 1px rgba(184,206,217,0.08);
    }

    /* ── Header ── */
    .card-header {
      padding: 2rem 2.5rem 1.75rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy-dark) 0%, #2a2068 100%);
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red);
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-end;
      gap: 1.25rem;
    }

    .header-icon {
      width: 48px;
      height: 48px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      background: var(--red);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .header-icon svg { width: 26px; height: 26px; fill: #fff; }

    .header-text h1 {
      font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
      font-size: 1.55rem;
      color: #fff;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .header-text p {
      margin-top: 0.3rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 300;
      color: var(--slate);
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    /* ── Table wrapper ── */
    .table-wrap {
      overflow-x: auto;
      padding: 0 0 0.5rem;
    }

    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
    }

    /* ── Column headers ── */
    thead tr {
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
    }

    thead th {
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--slate);
      text-align: left;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(184,206,217,0.12);
    }

    thead th:first-child { width: 22%; }
    thead th:nth-child(2),
    thead th:nth-child(3) { width: 39%; }

    /* pill labels in header */
    thead th .pill {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.2em 0.7em;
      border-radius: 99px;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      margin-top: 0.35rem;
    }
    .pill-gcs { background: rgba(109,58,133,0.3); color: #c89fdf; border: 1px solid rgba(109,58,133,0.6); }
    .pill-pcs { background: rgba(215,40,47,0.2);  color: #f0888b; border: 1px solid rgba(215,40,47,0.5); }

    /* ── Body rows ── */
    tbody tr {
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(184,206,217,0.07);
      transition: background 0.15s ease;
    }
    tbody tr:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    tbody tr:hover { background: rgba(184,206,217,0.04); }

    td {
      padding: 1.05rem 1.5rem;
      vertical-align: top;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: var(--silver);
    }

    /* Feature label cell */
    td:first-child {
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--slate);
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

    /* Alternating subtle row tint */
    tbody tr:nth-child(even) { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.12); }
    tbody tr:nth-child(even):hover { background: rgba(184,206,217,0.04); }

    /* Highlight key terms */
    em {
      font-style: normal;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #fff;
    }

    /* ── Footer ── */
    .card-footer {
      padding: 0.85rem 1.5rem;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(184,206,217,0.08);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .card-footer span {
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      color: var(--grey);
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .dot { width: 5px; height: 5px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="card">

  <div class="card-header">
    <div class="header-icon">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <path d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.477 2 12s4.477 10 10 10 10-4.477 10-10S17.523 2 12 2zm-1 17.93V18c0-.552-.448-1-1-1H8l-2-2v-2l2-2h3l1 1v1h2v-1l2-2v-1h-2v-1l-1-1H9l-1-1V7h2V6h1V4.07A8.001 8.001 0 0 1 20 12h-2l-1 1v2l-2 2h-2l-1-1v1l-1 1z"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <div class="header-text">
      <h1>Geographic vs Projected Coordinate Systems</h1>
      <p>Spatial Reference Fundamentals</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Feature</th>
          <th>
            Geographic Coordinate System
            <br/><span class="pill pill-gcs">GCS</span>
          </th>
          <th>
            Projected Coordinate System
            <br/><span class="pill pill-pcs">PCS</span>
          </th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Surface &amp; Shape</td>
          <td><em>3D and spherical</em> — based on an ellipsoid or globe model of the Earth</td>
          <td><em>2D and planar</em> — mathematically flattened onto a map surface</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Units of Measurement</td>
          <td><em>Angular units</em> — decimal degrees, or degrees / minutes / seconds</td>
          <td><em>Linear units</em> — metres or feet, enabling direct distance calculation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Distortion</td>
          <td>No distortion in <em>angular measurement</em>, but significant distortion in distance and area when displayed flat</td>
          <td>Always distorts <em>some</em> property — shape, area, distance, or direction — but allows localised accuracy suited to the projection's design</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Use Cases</td>
          <td>Storing spatial data, <em>GPS</em>, global datasets, data interchange (e.g. GDA2020 geographic, WGS84)</td>
          <td>Local maps, construction, engineering, <em>spatial analysis</em> — any task requiring accurate area or distance measurement (e.g. MGA Zone 55)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="card-footer">
    <div class="dot"></div>
    <span>GCS defines <em style="color:var(--silver)">where</em> on the globe &nbsp;·&nbsp; PCS defines <em style="color:var(--silver)">how</em> that location is drawn on a flat surface</span>
  </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>
